            "prompt": "You are an implementer subagent working on Phase 9 of the agent-tui project.\n\n**Task 9.3: Implement MCP tools panel in UI**\n\n**Full Task Text:**\nCreate a UI panel for displaying and managing MCP tools:\n1. Add MCP tools panel/sidebar in app.py\n2. Display discovered MCP tools\n3. Show MCP server status (connected/disconnected)\n4. Allow manual refresh of MCP tools\n5. Toggle to show/hide the panel\n\n**UI Design:**\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ MCP Tools                           [Refresh] [×]   │\n├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ 🔌 fetch-server              ● connected (3 tools)  │\n│   - fetch_url                                        │\n│   - fetch_html                                       │\n│   - extract_content                                  │\n│                                                      │\n│ 🔌 filesystem-server          ● connected (4 tools)   │\n│   - read_file                                        │\n│   - write_file                                       │\n│   - list_directory                                   │\n│   - search_files                                     │\n│                                                      │\n│ 🔌 calculator-server          ○ disconnected        │\n├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ Config: .mcp.json                                    │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n**Implementation Requirements:**\n\n1. **MCPPanel Widget** - New file: `src/agent_tui/entrypoints/widgets/mcp_panel.py`\n   - Extend ` textual.widgets.Static` or `Container`\n   - Display list of MCP servers\n   - Show server status (connected/disconnected)\n   - List tools under each server\n   - Refresh button to reload MCP config\n   - Close button to hide panel\n\n2. **Integration in app.py**\n   - Add toggle button in main UI (e.g., in header or sidebar)\n   - Method to show/hide MCP panel\n   - Integration with MCPToolManager from mcp.py\n   - Update panel when MCP tools are discovered\n\n3. **Data Binding**\n   - Connect to MCPToolManager.servers dict\n   - Display real-time server status\n   - Show tool names and descriptions\n\n**Key Implementation Details:**\n\n```python\n# mcp_panel.py\nfrom textual.widgets import Static, Button, Label\nfrom textual.containers import Vertical, Horizontal\n\nclass MCPPanel(Static):\n    \"\"\"Panel displaying MCP servers and their tools.\"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(self, tool_manager: MCPToolManager | None = None):\n        self.tool_manager = tool_manager\n        super().__init__()\n    \n    def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:\n        \"\"\"Compose the panel UI.\"\"\"\n        yield Horizontal(\n            Label(\"MCP Tools\", classes=\"mcp-title\"),\n            Button(\"Refresh\", id=\"refresh-mcp\"),\n            Button(\"×\", id=\"close-mcp\"),\n            classes=\"mcp-header\"\n        )\n        yield Vertical(id=\"mcp-servers\")\n    \n    def on_mount(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Initialize panel on mount.\"\"\"\n        self.refresh_servers()\n    \n    def refresh_servers(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Refresh the list of MCP servers and tools.\"\"\"\n        servers_container = self.query_one(\"#mcp-servers\", Vertical)\n        servers_container.remove_children()\n        \n        if not self.tool_manager:\n            servers_container.mount(Label(\"No MCP configuration found\"))\n            return\n        \n        for server_name, server_info in self.tool_manager.servers.items():\n            status = \"●\" if server_info.get('connected') else \"○\"\n            tool_count = len(server_info.get('tools', []))\n            \n            server_label = Label(\n                f\"{status} {server_name} ({tool_count} tools)\",\n                classes=\"mcp-server\"\n            )\n            servers_container.mount(server_label)\n            \n            for tool_name in server_info.get('tools', []):\n                servers_container.mount(\n                    Label(f\"  - {tool_name}\", classes=\"mcp-tool\")\n                )\n    \n    def on_button_pressed(self, event: Button.Pressed) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Handle button presses.\"\"\"\n        if event.button.id == \"refresh-mcp\":\n            self.refresh_servers()\n        elif event.button.id == \"close-mcp\":\n            self.remove()\n\n\n# app.py integration\ndef show_mcp_panel(self) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Show the MCP tools panel.\"\"\"\n    from agent_tui.services.deep_agents.mcp import _active_managers\n    \n    # Get the first active manager (or create one)\n    manager = None\n    if _active_managers:\n        manager = _active_managers[0]\n    \n    panel = MCPPanel(tool_manager=manager)\n    self.mount(panel)\n```\n\n**Styling (CSS):**\n```css\n/* mcp_panel.css */\n.mcp-title {\n    text-style: bold;\n    width: 1fr;\n}\n\n.mcp-header {\n    height: 3;\n    padding: 0 1;\n}\n\n.mcp-server {\n    color: $primary;\n    margin: 1 0 0 1;\n}\n\n.mcp-tool {\n    color: $text-muted;\n    margin: 0 0 0 3;\n}\n```\n\n**Context:**\n- Worktree: /home/shako/REPOS/Indie-Hacking/agent-tui/.worktrees/phase-9-mcp-sandboxes\n- New file: src/agent_tui/entrypoints/widgets/mcp_panel.py\n- Modify: src/agent_tui/entrypoints/app.py (add toggle button and show method)\n- MCPToolManager from mcp.py is already implemented\n- Tests should be in tests/test_mcp_panel.py\n\n**Verification Checklist:**\n- [ ] MCPPanel widget displays correctly\n- [ ] Shows MCP servers with status indicators\n- [ ] Lists tools under each server\n- [ ] Refresh button reloads MCP config\n- [ ] Close button hides panel\n- [ ] Toggle button in main UI works\n- [ ] Panel updates when servers change\n- [ ] All tests pass\n- [ ] Styling follows app theme\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- Uses existing MCPToolManager from mcp.py\n- Uses _active_managers global for accessing current manager\n- Textual widgets: Static, Button, Label, Container\n\n