          "input": {
            "filePath": "/home/shako/REPOS/Indie-Hacking/agent-tui/docs/agent-tui-course.html",
            "newString": "    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen-heading\">Human-in-the-Loop: Interrupt &amp; Resume</h2>\n      <p class=\"module-subtitle\">Approval flow with LangGraph interrupts — Phase 8</p>\n      <p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-6);\">Phase 8 completes the <span class=\"term\" data-definition=\"Human-in-the-Loop (HITL) means the agent pauses for user approval before executing sensitive operations.\">Human-in-the-Loop</span> system by integrating LangGraph's interrupt/resume mechanism. When the agent encounters sensitive tools (execute, write_file, web_search), it pauses and waits for user approval.</p>\n      \n      <div class=\"comparison-table\" style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-8);\">\n        <table>\n          <thead>\n            <tr>\n              <th>Tool</th>\n              <th>Interrupt?</th>\n              <th>Why</th>\n            </tr>\n          </thead>\n          <tbody>\n            <tr>\n              <td><code>execute</code></td>\n              <td><span style=\"color: var(--color-accent)\">● Yes</span></td>\n              <td>Shell commands can modify system state</td>\n            </tr>\n            <tr>\n              <td><code>write_file</code></td>\n              <td><span style=\"color: var(--color-accent)\">● Yes</span></td>\n              <td>Creates or overwrites files</td>\n            </tr>\n            <tr>\n              <td><code>edit_file</code></td>\n              <td><span style=\"color: var(--color-accent)\">● Yes</span></td>\n              <td>Modifies existing files</td>\n            </tr>\n            <tr>\n              <td><code>web_search</code></td>\n              <td><span style=\"color: var(--color-accent)\">● Yes</span></td>\n              <td>External network calls</td>\n            </tr>\n            <tr>\n              <td><code>fetch_url</code></td>\n              <td><span style=\"color: var(--color-accent)\">● Yes</span></td>\n              <td>Downloads external content</td>\n            </tr>\n            <tr>\n              <td><code>read_file</code></td>\n              <td><span style=\"color: var(--color-success)\">○ No</span></td>\n              <td>Read-only, safe operation</td>\n            </tr>\n            <tr>\n              <td><code>glob</code>, <code>grep</code></td>\n              <td><span style=\"color: var(--color-success)\">○ No</span></td>\n              <td>Search operations are safe</td>\n            </tr>\n          </tbody>\n        </table>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"code-block animate-in\" style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-6);\">\n        <div class=\"code-header\">\n          <div class=\"code-dots\">\n            <span class=\"code-dot red\"></span>\n            <span class=\"code-dot yellow\"></span>\n            <span class=\"code-dot green\"></span>\n          </div>\n          <span class=\"code-filename\">services/deep_agents/adapter.py</span>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"code-content\">\n<pre style=\"margin: 0;\"><code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm);\"><span style=\"color: var(--color-code-comment)\"># Configure which tools trigger interrupts</span>\ninterrupt_on = InterruptOnConfig(\n    tools={\n        <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-string)\">\"execute\"</span>: <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-keyword)\">True</span>,       <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-comment)\"># Always interrupt on shell commands</span>\n        <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-string)\">\"write_file\"</span>: <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-keyword)\">True</span>,  <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-comment)\"># Interrupt on file writes</span>\n        <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-string)\">\"edit_file\"</span>: <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-keyword)\">True</span>,  <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-comment)\"># Interrupt on file edits</span>\n        <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-string)\">\"read_file\"</span>: <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-keyword)\">False</span>, <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-comment)\"># Auto-approve reads (safe)</span>\n        <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-string)\">\"web_search\"</span>: <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-keyword)\">True</span>,  <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-comment)\"># Interrupt on external calls</span>\n    }\n)\n\n<span style=\"color: var(--color-code-keyword)\">self</span>._agent = create_deep_agent(\n    ...\n    interrupt_on=interrupt_on,\n)</code></pre>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"pattern-cards stagger-children\" style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-8);\">\n        <div class=\"pattern-card animate-in\" style=\"--stagger-index: 0; border-top: 3px solid var(--color-actor-1)\">\n          <div class=\"pattern-icon\" style=\"background: var(--color-actor-1)\">⏸️</div>\n          <h4 class=\"pattern-title\">Interrupt</h4>\n          <p class=\"pattern-desc\">LangGraph hits a sensitive tool → emits <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">INTERRUPT</code> event → EventTranslator converts to <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">EventType.INTERRUPT</code></p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"pattern-card animate-in\" style=\"--stagger-index: 1; border-top: 3px solid var(--color-actor-3)\">\n          <div class=\"pattern-icon\" style=\"background: var(--color-actor-3)\">👤</div>\n          <h4 class=\"pattern-title\">Approve/Reject/Edit</h4>\n          <p class=\"pattern-desc\">TUI shows interrupt overlay → User chooses approve (y), reject (n), or edit (e) → Result sent back to adapter</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"pattern-card animate-in\" style=\"--stagger-index: 2; border-top: 3px solid var(--color-actor-2)\">\n          <div class=\"pattern-icon\" style=\"background: var(--color-actor-2)\">▶️</div>\n          <h4 class=\"pattern-title\">Resume</h4>\n          <p class=\"pattern-desc\">Adapter calls <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">approve_tool()</code> → LangGraph receives <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">Command(resume=...)</code> → Agent continues execution</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"callout callout-info\" style=\"margin-top: var(--space-6)\">\n        <div class=\"callout-icon\">🛡️</div>\n        <div class=\"callout-content\">\n          <strong class=\"callout-title\">Safety patterns are blocked automatically</strong>\n          <p>Before the interrupt overlay even appears, commands with dangerous patterns (<code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">$(...)</code>, <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">`...`</code>, <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">$VAR</code>, redirects) are auto-rejected. This happens in <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">services/adapter.py</code> using <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">contains_dangerous_patterns()</code>.</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen-heading\">The Interrupt Overlay UI</h2>\n      <p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-6);\">When an interrupt occurs, the TUI displays a modal overlay with tool details and approval options:</p>\n      \n      <div class=\"code-block animate-in\" style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-6); background: var(--color-surface);\">\n        <div style=\"padding: var(--space-6); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm); line-height: 1.8;\">\n          <div style=\"color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-4);\">┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐</div>\n          <div style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-2);\"><span style=\"color: var(--color-accent)\">⚠️</span> Tool Execution Requested</div>\n          <div style=\"color: var(--color-text-muted); margin: var(--space-4) 0;\">──────────────────────────────────────────</div>\n          <div style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-2);\">Tool: <strong>execute</strong></div>\n          <div style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-4);\">Command: ls -la</div>\n          <div style=\"color: var(--color-text-muted); margin: var(--space-4) 0;\">──────────────────────────────────────────</div>\n          <div style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-2);\"><strong>[y/1]</strong> Approve</div>\n          <div style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-2);\"><strong>[e/2]</strong> Edit (stub)</div>\n          <div style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-4);\"><strong>[n/3]</strong> Reject</div>\n          <div style=\"color: var(--color-text-muted);\">└─────────────────────────────────────────┘</div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-6);\">The overlay is implemented as a <span class=\"term\" data-definition=\"ModalScreen in Textual is a full-screen overlay that captures all input until dismissed.\">ModalScreen</span> widget with keyboard shortcuts:</p>\n\n      <div class=\"comparison-table\" style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-6);\">\n        <table>\n          <thead>\n            <tr>\n              <th>Key</th>\n              <th>Action</th>\n              <th>Result</th>\n            </tr>\n          </thead>\n          <tbody>\n            <tr>\n              <td><code>y</code> or <code>1</code></td>\n              <td>Approve</td>\n              <td>Tool executes, agent continues</td>\n            </tr>\n            <tr>\n              <td><code>n</code> or <code>3</code> or <code>Esc</code></td>\n              <td>Reject</td>\n              <td>Tool skipped, agent continues without result</td>\n            </tr>\n            <tr>\n              <td><code>e</code> or <code>2</code></td>\n              <td>Edit (stub)</td>\n              <td>Currently falls through to approve (future: modify args)</td>\n            </tr>\n          </tbody>\n        </table>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen-heading\">MCP &amp; Sandboxes: External Tools &amp; Isolation</h2>\n      <p class=\"module-subtitle\">MCP tool loading and sandboxed execution — Phase 9</p>\n      <p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-6);\">Phase 9 adds two major capabilities: <strong>MCP (Model Context Protocol)</strong> for connecting to external tool ecosystems, and <strong>Sandbox</strong> for isolated, secure execution.</p>\n\n      <div class=\"pattern-cards stagger-children\" style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-8);\">\n        <div class=\"pattern-card animate-in\" style=\"--stagger-index: 0; border-top: 3px solid var(--color-actor-4)\">\n          <div class=\"pattern-icon\" style=\"background: var(--color-actor-4)\">🔌</div>\n          <h4 class=\"pattern-title\">MCP Integration</h4>\n          <p class=\"pattern-desc\">Parse <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">.mcp.json</code> → Start MCP servers as subprocesses → Discover tools via MCP protocol → Register with DeepAgents</p>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"pattern-card animate-in\" style=\"--stagger-index: 1; border-top: 3px solid var(--color-actor-5)\">\n          <div class=\"pattern-icon\" style=\"background: var(--color-actor-5)\">🏝️</div>\n          <h4 class=\"pattern-title\">Sandbox Isolation</h4>\n          <p class=\"pattern-desc\">All file/shell operations contained in sandbox directory → Path traversal blocked → Host system protected</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen-heading\">The Model Context Protocol (MCP)</h2>\n      <p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-6);\"><span class=\"term\" data-definition=\"Model Context Protocol (MCP) is an open protocol that standardizes how applications provide context to LLMs — like a USB-C port for AI applications.\">MCP</span> allows the agent to connect to external tool servers. Each server provides tools, resources, and prompts via a standardized protocol.</p>\n\n      <div class=\"code-block animate-in\" style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-6);\">\n        <div class=\"code-header\">\n          <div class=\"code-dots\">\n            <span class=\"code-dot red\"></span>\n            <span class=\"code-dot yellow\"></span>\n            <span class=\"code-dot green\"></span>\n          </div>\n          <span class=\"code-filename\">.mcp.json</span>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"code-content\">\n<pre style=\"margin: 0;\"><code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm);\">{\n  <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-string)\">\"servers\"</span>: {\n    <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-string)\">\"fetch\"</span>: {\n      <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-string)\">\"command\"</span>: <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-string-literal)\">\"uvx\"</span>,\n      <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-string)\">\"args\"</span>: [<span style=\"color: var(--color-code-string-literal)\">\"mcp-server-fetch\"</span>]\n    },\n    <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-string)\">\"filesystem\"</span>: {\n      <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-string)\">\"command\"</span>: <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-string-literal)\">\"npx\"</span>,\n      <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-string)\">\"args\"</span>: [<span style=\"color: var(--color-code-string-literal)\">\"-y\"</span>, <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-string-literal)\">\"@modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem\"</span>, <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-string-literal)\">\"/allowed/path\"</span>]\n    }\n  }\n}</code></pre>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"callout callout-success\" style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-6)\">\n        <div class=\"callout-icon\">🔄</div>\n        <div class=\"callout-content\">\n          <strong class=\"callout-title\">MCP Tool Flow</strong>\n          <p>User has <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">.mcp.json</code> → MCPToolManager parses config → Starts servers via stdio → Discovers tools via MCP protocol → Converts to LangChain tools → Registers with <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">create_deep_agent(tools=...)</code> → Agent can call MCP tools like native tools</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-6);\">MCP tools integrate seamlessly with Phase 8's HITL system — they can be configured to require approval just like native tools.</p>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen-heading\">MCP Tools Panel</h2>\n      <p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-6);\">The TUI provides a sidebar panel for monitoring MCP servers and their tools:</p>\n\n      <div class=\"code-block animate-in\" style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-6); background: var(--color-surface);\">\n        <div style=\"padding: var(--space-6); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm); line-height: 1.8;\">\n          <div style=\"display: flex; justify-content: space-between; margin-bottom: var(--space-4);\">\n            <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">MCP Tools</span>\n            <span><span style=\"color: var(--color-text-muted);\">[Refresh] [×]</span></span>\n          </div>\n          <div style=\"color: var(--color-text-muted); margin: var(--space-4) 0;\">────────────────────────────</div>\n          <div style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-2);\"><span style=\"color: var(--color-success);\">●</span> fetch-server (3 tools)</div>\n          <div style=\"margin-left: var(--space-4); color: var(--color-text-muted);\">- fetch_url</div>\n          <div style=\"margin-left: var(--space-4); color: var(--color-text-muted);\">- fetch_html</div>\n          <div style=\"margin-left: var(--space-4); color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-4);\">- extract_content</div>\n          <div style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-2);\"><span style=\"color: var(--color-success);\">●</span> filesystem-server (4 tools)</div>\n          <div style=\"margin-left: var(--space-4); color: var(--color-text-muted);\">- read_file</div>\n          <div style=\"margin-left: var(--space-4); color: var(--color-text-muted);\">- write_file</div>\n          <div style=\"margin-left: var(--space-4); color: var(--color-text-muted);\">- list_directory</div>\n          <div style=\"margin-left: var(--space-4); color: var(--color-text-muted);\">- search_files</div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-6);\">The panel uses Textual's <span class=\"term\" data-definition=\"Reactive data in Textual automatically triggers UI updates when the underlying data changes.\">reactive data binding</span> to update in real-time as server status changes.</p>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen-heading\">Sandbox Isolation</h2>\n      <p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-6);\">The <span class=\"term\" data-definition=\"SandboxBackend provides isolated execution where all file and shell operations are contained within a sandbox directory.\">SandboxBackend</span> ensures all agent operations stay within a designated directory, protecting the host system.</p>\n\n      <div class=\"code-block animate-in\" style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-6);\">\n        <div class=\"code-header\">\n          <div class=\"code-dots\">\n            <span class=\"code-dot red\"></span>\n            <span class=\"code-dot yellow\"></span>\n            <span class=\"code-dot green\"></span>\n          </div>\n          <span class=\"code-filename\">services/deep_agents/sandbox.py</span>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"code-content\">\n<pre style=\"margin: 0;\"><code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm);\"><span style=\"color: var(--color-code-keyword)\">def</span> <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-function)\">_resolve_path</span>(<span style=\"color: var(--color-code-keyword)\">self</span>, path: <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-type)\">str</span>) -> Path:\n    <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-comment)\">\"\"\"Resolve path within sandbox, blocking traversal attacks.\"\"\"</span>\n    <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-comment)\"># Handle absolute paths by stripping leading /</span>\n    <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-keyword)\">if</span> path.startswith(<span style=\"color: var(--color-code-string-literal)\">\"/\"</span>):\n        path = path[<span style=\"color: var(--color-code-number)\">1</span>:]\n    \n    <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-comment)\"># Resolve relative to sandbox root</span>\n    target = (<span style=\"color: var(--color-code-keyword)\">self</span>.root_dir / path).resolve()\n    \n    <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-comment)\"># Security check: ensure resolved path is within sandbox</span>\n    <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-keyword)\">try</span>:\n        target.relative_to(<span style=\"color: var(--color-code-keyword)\">self</span>.root_dir.resolve())\n    <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-keyword)\">except</span> ValueError:\n        <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-keyword)\">raise</span> ValueError(<span style=\"color: var(--color-code-string)\">f\"Path '{path}' attempts to escape sandbox\"</span>)\n    \n    <span style=\"color: var(--color-code-keyword)\">return</span> target</code></pre>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"comparison-table\" style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-6);\">\n        <table>\n          <thead>\n            <tr>\n              <th>Path Requested</th>\n              <th>Resolved To</th>\n              <th>Result</th>\n            </tr>\n          </thead>\n          <tbody>\n            <tr>\n              <td><code>/etc/passwd</code></td>\n              <td><code>sandbox/etc/passwd</code></td>\n              <td><span style=\"color: var(--color-success)\">✓ Contained</span></td>\n            </tr>\n            <tr>\n              <td><code>../../../etc/passwd</code></td>\n              <td>—</td>\n              <td><span style=\"color: var(--color-error)\">✗ Blocked (traversal)</span></td>\n            </tr>\n            <tr>\n              <td><code>../secret.txt</code></td>\n              <td>—</td>\n              <td><span style=\"color: var(--color-error)\">✗ Blocked (escape attempt)</span></td>\n            </tr>\n            <tr>\n              <td><code>project/src/main.py</code></td>\n              <td><code>sandbox/project/src/main.py</code></td>\n              <td><span style=\"color: var(--color-success)\">✓ Contained</span></td>\n            </tr>\n          </tbody>\n        </table>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"callout callout-error\" style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-6)\">\n        <div class=\"callout-icon\">🛡️</div>\n        <div class=\"callout-content\">\n          <strong class=\"callout-title\">Path Traversal Protection</strong>\n          <p>The <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">_resolve_path()</code> method uses <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">Path.resolve()</code> to normalize paths and <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">relative_to()</code> to verify the resolved path is within the sandbox root. Any attempt to escape (via <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">../</code> or absolute paths) raises <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">ValueError</code>.</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen-heading\">Sandbox vs Host Execution</h2>\n      <p style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-6);\">The TUI can use either sandboxed or direct host execution:</p>\n\n      <div class=\"comparison-table\" style=\"margin-bottom: var(--space-8);\">\n        <table>\n          <thead>\n            <tr>\n              <th>Backend</th>\n              <th>Use Case</th>\n              <th>Isolation</th>\n              <th>Persistence</th>\n            </tr>\n          </thead>\n          <tbody>\n            <tr>\n              <td><strong>LocalShellBackend</strong></td>\n              <td>Direct host access</td>\n              <td>None (virtual_mode=True for paths)</td>\n              <td>Files persist in cwd</td>\n            </tr>\n            <tr>\n              <td><strong>SandboxBackend</strong></td>\n              <td>Isolated execution</td>\n              <td>Full (directory-based sandbox)</td>\n              <td>Files in .agent-sandbox/</td>\n            </tr>\n          </tbody>\n        </table>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"callout callout-info\">\n        <div class=\"callout-icon\">💡</div>\n        <div class=\"callout-content\">\n          <strong class=\"callout-title\">When to use each backend</strong>\n          <p>Use <strong>LocalShellBackend</strong> for trusted environments where the agent needs full project access. Use <strong>SandboxBackend</strong> when running untrusted code, testing, or when you want to isolate agent operations. Both respect the <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">cleanup</code> flag — set to <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">True</code> to auto-remove sandbox on exit, <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm)\">False</code> to inspect results.</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <h2 class=\"screen-heading\">Quiz: MCP &amp; Sandboxes</h2>\n      <div class=\"quiz-container\" id=\"quiz-11\">\n        <div class=\"quiz-question-block\" data-question=\"q1\" data-correct=\"option-b\">\n          <h3 class=\"quiz-question\">A user has this <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono)\">.mcp.json</code>: <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono)\">{\"servers\": {\"calc\": {\"command\": \"python\", \"args\": [\"calc_server.py\"]}}}</code>. The server provides a tool called \"calculate\". How does the TUI access it?</h3>\n          <div class=\"quiz-options\">\n            <button class=\"quiz-option\" data-value=\"option-a\" onclick=\"selectOption(this)\">\n              <div class=\"quiz-option-radio\"></div>\n              <span>Direct import of calc_server.py as a Python module</span>\n            </button>\n            <button class=\"quiz-option\" data-value=\"option-b\" onclick=\"selectOption(this)\">\n              <div class=\"quiz-option-radio\"></div>\n              <span>MCPToolManager starts the server as a subprocess and discovers tools via MCP protocol</span>\n            </button>\n            <button class=\"quiz-option\" data-value=\"option-c\" onclick=\"selectOption(this)\">\n              <div class=\"quiz-option-radio\"></div>\n              <span>The TUI reads the JSON and creates a mock tool that doesn't actually execute</span>\n            </button>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"quiz-feedback\" id=\"q1-feedback-11\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"quiz-question-block\" data-question=\"q2\" data-correct=\"option-a\">\n          <h3 class=\"quiz-question\">An agent in a SandboxBackend tries to write to <code style=\"font-family: var(--font-mono)\">../../../etc/passwd</code>. What happens?</h3>\n          <div class=\"quiz-options\">\n            <button class=\"quiz-option\" data-value=\"option-a\" onclick=\"selectOption(this)\">\n              <div class=\"quiz-option-radio\"></div>\n              <span>ValueError is raised: \"Path attempts to escape sandbox\"</span>\n            </button>\n            <button class=\"quiz-option\" data-value=\"option-b\" onclick=\"selectOption(this)\">\n              <div class=\"quiz-option-radio\"></div>\n              <span>The file is written to /etc/passwd on the host system</span>\n            </button>\n            <button class=\"quiz-option\" data-value=\"option-c\" onclick=\"selectOption(this)\">\n              <div class=\"quiz-option-radio\"></div>\n              <span>The path is normalized and written to sandbox/etc/passwd</span>\n            </button>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"quiz-feedback\" id=\"q2-feedback-11\"></div>\n        </div>\n        <button class=\"quiz-check-btn\" onclick=\"checkQuiz('quiz-11')\">Check Answers</button>\n        <button class=\"quiz-reset-btn\" onclick=\"resetQuiz('quiz-11')\">Try Again</button>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"screen animate-in\">\n      <div class=\"callout callout-accent\">\n        <div class=\"callout-icon\">🎓</div>\n        <div class=\"callout-content\">\n          <strong class=\"callout-title\">You've completed the full course!</strong>\n          <p>From the approval system to web search, subagent delegation, context management, persistent memory, Human-in-the-Loop interrupts, MCP integration, and sandbox isolation — you now understand how agent-tui extends a basic TUI into a full agent interface. The patterns repeat: intercept special tool names early, emit semantic events, keep the UI layer thin. Build on these three rules and you can add any capability.</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</section>",
